# Date-Only Field Handling

All date-only fields (no time component) MUST be stored at **noon UTC** (`T12:00:00.000Z`) to prevent day-off-by-one bugs in timezones west of UTC.

## The Problem

`new Date("2026-01-23")` produces `2026-01-23T00:00:00.000Z` (midnight UTC). In `America/New_York` (UTC-5), `format(new Date("2026-01-23T00:00:00.000Z"), "MMM d, yyyy")` displays **"Jan 22, 2026"** ‚Äî one day earlier than intended.

## Required Patterns

### API routes ‚Äî storing date-only values

Use `parseDateOnly()` from `@/lib/date-utils`. NEVER use `new Date(dateString)` for date-only fields.

```typescript
import { parseDateOnly } from "@/lib/date-utils";

// Correct
startDate: parseDateOnly(validatedData.startDate)!,
endDate: validatedData.endDate ? parseDateOnly(validatedData.endDate) : null,

// WRONG ‚Äî produces midnight UTC
startDate: new Date(validatedData.startDate),
```

### Seed files ‚Äî constructing date literals

Use the local `noonUTC()` helper:

```typescript
function noonUTC(dateStr: string): Date {
  const [year, month, day] = dateStr.split("-").map(Number);
  return new Date(Date.UTC(year, month - 1, day, 12, 0, 0, 0));
}

birthDate: noonUTC("2016-03-15"),
```

### Frontend forms ‚Äî `<input type="date">` handlers

Parse the `YYYY-MM-DD` value to noon UTC, or keep it as a string and let the API handle parsing:

```typescript
// Option A: construct noon UTC in the handler
const [y, m, d] = e.target.value.split("-").map(Number);
const date = new Date(Date.UTC(y, m - 1, d, 12, 0, 0, 0));

// Option B (preferred): keep as string, send YYYY-MM-DD to API
setFormData(prev => ({ ...prev, startDate: e.target.value }));
```

### Frontend display ‚Äî constructing dates from strings for formatting

Append `T12:00:00Z` instead of `T00:00:00`:

```typescript
// Correct
const dateObj = new Date(dateString + "T12:00:00Z");

// WRONG ‚Äî may shift in western timezones
const dateObj = new Date(dateString + "T00:00:00");
```

## Date-only vs. datetime fields

**Date-only** (use `parseDateOnly` / noon UTC): `birthDate`, `startDate`, `endDate`, `dueDate`, `hireDate`, `date` (events/shifts/evaluations), `validFrom`, `validTo`, `purchaseDate`, `lastInspectionDate`, `autoRenewDate`, `targetDate`, `nextChargeDate`, `scheduledGoLiveDate`

**True datetimes** (use `new Date()` as-is): `createdAt`, `updatedAt`, `lastActiveAt`, `scheduledAt` (campaigns), `checkedIn`, `settledAt`, `paidAt`, `expiresAt` (tokens/sessions)

## Canonical utilities

All date utilities live in `src/lib/date-utils.ts`:

| Function | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `parseDateOnly(str)` | Parse `YYYY-MM-DD` ‚Üí noon UTC Date |
| `normalizeToNoonUTC(date)` | Fix midnight UTC ‚Üí noon UTC |
| `formatDateOnly(date, tz?)` | Format Date ‚Üí `YYYY-MM-DD` |
| `getTodayNoonUTC()` | Today at noon UTC |
| `isSameDay(d1, d2)` | Compare calendar days in UTC |
